race.comment: TRicky. DETERMINATION (5) resumed further improved placing this track/trip in a CL1. Maps for the run of the race and has some weight relief in this grade. Proven second-up and can go one better. MELO MELO KAVA (3) had been around the mark before his nose defeat at Townsville in a CL3. Has to drop back to a shorter sprint but he draws handy and this is a suitable assignment. RUM RUMBLE (7) resumed as a short priced favourite in a 55 at Mackay and didn't do a bad job after missing the kick and settling rearward. Has to push over from a the outside gate but gets in light with the 3kg claim and with average luck he can make the finish. DALT JAZ (2) turned his form around at Townsville winning a 55. He's back in trip and will be giving away a start. Regardless, the claim is handy and he's in the mix.
